    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-09-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="449" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                <head>No. 450.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Phelps</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-09-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 21, 1883</date>. (Received
                            October 16.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 6.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge receipt of
                        your dispatch No. 8, with the inclosed copy of Mr. Logan’s note concerning
                        the terms of the proposed treaty of peace as negotiated between Mr. Novoa
                        and General Iglesias.</p>
                <pb facs="0787" n="717" xml:id="pg_717"/>
                <p>The importance of the subject-matter of this dispatch is fully recognized,
                        and I shall give it the most earnest and careful attention.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S. L. PHELPS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
